content: /*<![CDATA[*/ $('#title').html($('meta[name=map-description]').attr('content')); /*]]>*/ Endpoint Security Supports Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9 (ARM64) June 25, 2025—Trend Vision One Endpoint Security now supports Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9 (ARM64). Both Server & Workload Protection and Endpoint Sensor now support deploying to Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9 (ARM64) endpoints. When deploying a new agent in Endpoint Inventory, you can now select Red Hat Enterprise Linux 9 (ARM64). For details on supported Linux platforms, see Endpoint Agent System Requirements.
